WEBVTT

00:00.416 --> 00:03.116
<i>My name is Michael Westen.</i>
<i>I used to be a spy until...</i>

00:04.527 --> 00:07.062
We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.

00:07.667 --> 00:10.035
<i>When you're burned,</i>
<i>you've got nothing --</i>

00:10.103 --> 00:12.605
<i>no cash, no credit,</i>
<i>no job history.</i>

00:12.672 --> 00:14.940
<i>You're stuck in whatever city</i>
<i>they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:15.008 --> 00:17.109
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:17.177 --> 00:20.346
<i>You do whatever work</i>
<i>comes your way.</i>

00:20.413 --> 00:22.982
<i>You rely on anyone</i>
<i>who's still talking to you.</i>

00:23.049 --> 00:24.583
<i>A trigger-happy</i>
<i>ex-girlfriend...</i>

00:24.651 --> 00:26.218
Should we shoot them?

00:26.286 --> 00:28.787
<i>...An old friend who used</i>
<i>to inform on you to the FBI...</i>

00:28.855 --> 00:31.190
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.258 --> 00:33.659
<i>...Family, too...</i>
<i>Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:33.727 --> 00:35.895
<i>...If you're desperate.</i>
<i>Someone needs your help, Michael.</i>

00:35.962 --> 00:38.397
<i>Bottom line --</i>
<i>as long as you're burned,</i>

00:38.465 --> 00:40.065
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

00:45.002 --> 00:48.605
Six years ago, your substitute
therapist was Anson Fullerton.

00:48.672 --> 00:50.006
Who the hell are you?

00:50.074 --> 00:51.441
The organization
that burned you,

00:51.508 --> 00:53.142
I'm the last
one of them.

00:55.246 --> 00:57.080
Anson is the one
who killed Benny.

00:59.583 --> 01:01.484
You're not the only one
he got close to.

01:01.552 --> 01:04.354
You know, Michael, you shouldn't
be so hard on your old man.

01:04.421 --> 01:07.423
He wasn't quite the poisonous
leech you make him out to be.

01:07.491 --> 01:09.359
What makes you
such an expert?

01:09.426 --> 01:12.262
All those years, how many times
did you wish he were dead?

01:12.329 --> 01:14.597
We did it for you.
You're welcome, Michael.

01:22.866 --> 01:26.608
<i>A spy's life rarely starts</i>
<i>with a happy childhood.</i>

01:26.609 --> 01:28.777
<i>The fact is,</i>
<i>the best preparation</i>

01:28.845 --> 01:31.547
<i>for a career filled</i>
<i>with danger and paranoia</i>

01:31.614 --> 01:35.117
<i>is a home life filled with</i>
<i>danger and paranoia.</i>

01:35.185 --> 01:37.786
<i>It makes for a complex</i>
<i>relationship with the past,</i>

01:37.854 --> 01:39.288
<i>under the best</i>
<i>of circumstances.</i>

01:39.356 --> 01:42.691
God...I haven't been here
since we buried him.

01:42.759 --> 01:45.027
Your father
would hate this place.

01:45.095 --> 01:46.729
I can just see him
yelling at some gardener

01:46.796 --> 01:47.963
about all the weeds.

01:50.834 --> 01:53.502
I still can't believe
he died to protect you.

01:53.570 --> 01:55.404
Mom, we heard that
from a murderer

01:55.472 --> 01:57.172
who framed Fiona
for a bombing.

01:57.240 --> 01:59.508
I'm not sure we can
take Anson's word far it.

01:59.576 --> 02:00.909
Maybe not.

02:00.977 --> 02:04.213
But I remember,
just before Frank died,

02:04.280 --> 02:08.183
he was asking about you,
out of the blue.

02:08.251 --> 02:10.818
I didn't have time
to find it odd.

02:12.322 --> 02:15.290
In a week, I was trying to
figure out why he'd gotten drunk

02:15.358 --> 02:16.592
and O.D.'d on heart pills.

02:16.659 --> 02:18.127
I'm telling you,
Michael, it fits.

02:18.194 --> 02:19.495
No, ma, listen.

02:19.562 --> 02:21.330
This is just Anson
trying to get into my head.

02:21.398 --> 02:22.898
No, you listen.

02:22.966 --> 02:26.935
I'm not a spy,
but I'm not a total idiot.

02:27.003 --> 02:28.904
They used Frank
to learn about you.

02:28.972 --> 02:31.073
And when he caught on,
they killed him.

02:31.141 --> 02:33.108
He was a bad man,
Michael.

02:33.176 --> 02:34.843
But even he
had his moments.

02:34.911 --> 02:38.414
Nate's rented a place up
in Daytona Beach for a week.

02:38.481 --> 02:42.184
I'm gonna take off and go up
there, take some time, you know,

02:42.252 --> 02:44.653
try and get used to this.

02:44.721 --> 02:46.388
How do you
get used to this?

02:49.292 --> 02:50.592
You look at me.

02:50.660 --> 02:52.728
You have a job to do.

02:52.796 --> 02:54.196
Make sure Anson
doesn't ruin any more lives.

02:56.199 --> 03:00.035
I'm just not...
I'm not sure how to do that.

03:00.103 --> 03:02.471
Figure it out,
Michael.

03:02.539 --> 03:04.807
You do
whatever you have to do.

03:08.945 --> 03:10.779
How'd it go?

03:10.847 --> 03:13.282
Well, I think I have just
the thing to make you smile.

03:13.349 --> 03:16.285
We finally got something
on Anson I think we can use.

03:16.352 --> 03:17.820
You know how
we thought his money

03:17.887 --> 03:19.388
was completely untraceable?

03:19.456 --> 03:21.423
Well,
that spiky-haired weasel Barry

03:21.491 --> 03:23.225
managed to
make himself useful.

03:23.293 --> 03:25.127
I needed someone sneaky enough
to track the money

03:25.195 --> 03:26.728
without anyone knowing,
especially Anson.

03:26.796 --> 03:28.964
He traced a few mil through
half a dozen shell corporations

03:29.032 --> 03:31.633
into a
Chinese brokerage account,

03:31.701 --> 03:33.368
and finally
a D.C. law firm.

03:33.436 --> 03:35.537
Fi...
Already packed.

03:39.309 --> 03:42.010
<i>Law firms are used to run</i>
<i>all sorts of shady businesses</i>

03:42.078 --> 03:44.246
<i>for good reason.</i>

03:44.314 --> 03:46.248
<i>They're discrete, powerful,</i>
<i>and protected.</i>

03:46.316 --> 03:48.717
<i>Between the high security</i>
<i>and privacy rules,</i>

03:48.785 --> 03:52.221
<i>getting intel from a law office</i>
<i>is more or less impossible,</i>

03:52.288 --> 03:53.655
<i>unless you're willing</i>
<i>to break those rules.</i>

03:53.723 --> 03:56.692
Check out the lady
in the gray skirt suit.

03:56.759 --> 03:58.794
You think you can
match that look by lunch?

03:58.862 --> 04:02.030
You just worry about
getting that badge.

04:05.568 --> 04:07.870
Excuse me. Can you help me?
I am so lost.

04:07.937 --> 04:09.371
I am looking
for the Smithsonian

04:09.439 --> 04:11.106
- I'm a member. First time in D.C.
- Okay.

04:11.174 --> 04:13.041
- I'm very excited, so I got a little lost.
- Uh-huh.

04:13.109 --> 04:14.409
I was on New York.

04:14.477 --> 04:17.144
I made a right on Pennsylvania
and a left on Virginia,

04:17.213 --> 04:18.814
and somehow
I got off constitution.

04:18.882 --> 04:20.214
Oh, there it is --
Smithsonian.

04:20.283 --> 04:22.217
Thank you so much. Can't believe
it was right there.

04:22.285 --> 04:24.219
Yeah, no...problem.

04:24.287 --> 04:27.556
<i>If you can find someone who</i>
<i>fits your general description</i>

04:27.624 --> 04:29.391
<i>and borrow</i>
<i>their identification,</i>

04:29.459 --> 04:31.393
<i>the perfect wig</i>
<i>and a new pair of glasses</i>

04:31.461 --> 04:33.896
<i>can get you a free ticket</i>
<i>to look around.</i>

04:33.963 --> 04:36.532
<i>At least until the firm's</i>
<i>lawyers get back from lunch.</i>

04:36.599 --> 04:38.667
He's with me.

04:40.436 --> 04:43.739
There's no "Anson" or
"Fullerton" in the client files.

04:43.806 --> 04:45.173
You see anything?

04:45.241 --> 04:46.775
Nothing useful.

04:46.843 --> 04:48.110
Just indecipherable financial
documents and property deeds.

04:48.177 --> 04:50.245
Keep looking.
Might be under a different name.

04:50.313 --> 04:51.747
Well, I hardly see
any names at all.

04:51.814 --> 04:53.348
Just references
to other file numbers.

04:53.416 --> 04:55.851
Keeping names off documents
is a good idea

04:55.919 --> 04:58.654
when your clients are running
black ops and killing people.

05:00.256 --> 05:02.057
What do you got?
Find something on Anson?

05:02.125 --> 05:05.127
Not Anson.
But recognize him?

05:08.765 --> 05:10.065
It's been a while.

05:10.133 --> 05:12.568
Michael Westen, you made
a big mistake crossing me.

05:12.635 --> 05:15.337
Now you're gonna see what it's
like having me for an enemy.

05:15.405 --> 05:18.807
Fi, this file was updated
two days ago. It's active.

05:18.875 --> 05:21.543
What does Anson want with a man
who's locked in prison for life?

05:21.611 --> 05:25.438
Find that out, and we're
one step ahead of Anson.

05:25.538 --> 05:29.038
<font color=#00FF00>Burn Notice 5x17</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Acceptable Loss</font>
Original Air Date on December 8, 2011

05:29.039 --> 05:32.489
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

05:32.508 --> 05:34.104
Man, I thought
I saw the last of this guy

05:34.105 --> 05:35.338
when we sent him
to prison.

05:35.406 --> 05:37.541
I mean, you really think
he's working with Anson?

05:37.608 --> 05:39.609
Vaughn's locked in the
darkest hole the government has.

05:39.677 --> 05:41.111
He's not
talking to anyone.

05:41.178 --> 05:43.880
Which means Anson's working on
his own, moving Vaughn's assets.

05:43.948 --> 05:45.515
Yeah, but these
so-called "assets"

05:45.583 --> 05:47.450
look just like
more meaningless numbers.

05:47.518 --> 05:50.153
I mean, there's no way to know
what Anson's up to.

05:50.221 --> 05:51.655
Unless I talk to Vaughn.

05:51.722 --> 05:53.924
Excuse me? You planning a trip
to Guantanamo?

05:53.991 --> 05:56.826
No, Pearce can have the CIA
bring Vaughn here for a chat.

05:56.894 --> 05:58.261
I need to call Jesse,

05:58.329 --> 06:01.064
see if his firm can turn
these numbers into names.

06:01.132 --> 06:03.300
I don't want to talk to Vaughn
without doing my homework.

06:03.367 --> 06:04.200
Amen to that, brother.

06:08.506 --> 06:10.774
No, it's no problem, Mike.
Just send me the documents.

06:10.841 --> 06:12.475
I'll put
the research department on it.

06:12.543 --> 06:14.077
And this needs to
stay quiet.

06:14.145 --> 06:16.246
Yeah. What doesn't with you,
man? Please.

06:16.314 --> 06:21.017
Look, I got my friend's
retirement...party right now.

06:21.085 --> 06:22.852
I'll check in later.

06:22.920 --> 06:24.220
Yeah.

06:30.194 --> 06:32.228
Ian.

06:32.296 --> 06:34.331
I thought you said
this was a party, man.

06:34.398 --> 06:35.565
Where's everybody at?

06:35.633 --> 06:37.233
Invitation said a gathering,
not a party.

06:37.301 --> 06:38.902
You're the only one
that got it, Porter.

06:38.970 --> 06:40.837
Have a seat.

06:40.905 --> 06:42.606
So I take it
there's no cake.

06:42.673 --> 06:44.307
What are you drinking?

06:44.375 --> 06:46.176
Just whatever
he's having.

06:49.180 --> 06:51.615
What's up?

06:51.682 --> 06:53.116
Question --

06:53.184 --> 06:54.718
I've heard the stories
about what you've been up to

06:54.785 --> 06:56.186
since you left CIFA,

06:56.253 --> 06:58.788
you and that guy Westen
kicking ass.

06:58.856 --> 07:00.023
Those stories true?

07:00.091 --> 07:03.493
Um...Yeah. Yeah.
Most of them.

07:03.561 --> 07:04.728
Good.

07:04.795 --> 07:06.863
I'm leaving
government work, too,

07:06.931 --> 07:09.199
and I know somebody
that needs an ass-kicking.

07:09.266 --> 07:11.835
It's Yash Ahluwalia,

07:11.902 --> 07:14.404
diplomat
with the Indian consulate.

07:14.472 --> 07:17.107
State department
assigned me to him in 2002.

07:17.174 --> 07:19.442
Said they needed their "best"
working with him.

07:19.510 --> 07:22.746
I spend most of my time
sorting out his parking tickets,

07:22.813 --> 07:24.914
keeping him out of jail
when he roughs up a call girl.

07:24.982 --> 07:27.083
Covering for diplomats
is kind of part of your gig.

07:27.151 --> 07:28.818
You may not like it,
but it is what it is.

07:28.886 --> 07:30.987
And one more thing.

07:31.055 --> 07:33.189
I'm helping him
smuggle diamonds.

07:33.257 --> 07:36.426
Okay.

07:36.494 --> 07:40.296
Okay. If you're doing something
illegal, I can't help you.

07:40.364 --> 07:42.932
That's just it. Under the
Vienna Convention, it's legal.

07:43.000 --> 07:44.234
He does it
all under diplomatic cover.

07:44.301 --> 07:47.003
Cops can't touch him.

07:47.071 --> 07:48.471
And guess
who authorizes it all.

07:48.539 --> 07:50.607
What about you boss? Why can't
you just talk to him about it?

07:50.675 --> 07:53.209
I already tried that.

07:53.277 --> 07:55.612
Station chief said to
hold my nose and do my job.

07:55.680 --> 07:57.147
And I did.

07:57.214 --> 08:02.719
Until I got tired of waking up

08:02.787 --> 08:03.720
and seeing crap like this.

08:08.025 --> 08:11.094
It's not just smuggling.
He's getting away with murder.

08:11.162 --> 08:13.363
Listen, Jesse,
I've seen all the proof.

08:13.431 --> 08:15.365
Every time he does a deal,

08:15.433 --> 08:18.735
he takes me and the buyer
into a secure room.

08:18.803 --> 08:20.370
While I'm filling out
documents,

08:20.438 --> 08:22.739
I'm sitting right next to
all the evidence --

08:22.807 --> 08:24.107
falsified certificates,

08:24.175 --> 08:26.676
diplomatic pouches
full of raw diamonds, all of it.

08:26.744 --> 08:29.713
He's got a sale
coming up this week.

08:29.780 --> 08:32.649
If I can get that evidence,
I can take him down.

08:32.717 --> 08:34.551
Ian, do you know
what you're getting into?

08:34.618 --> 08:36.453
You're gonna lose your job.
You're gonna lose your pension.

08:36.520 --> 08:37.899
You can end up in jail
yourself. This is --

08:37.924 --> 08:39.089
I don't care!

08:39.090 --> 08:42.125
People are dying.
I don't want to retire

08:42.193 --> 08:46.429
knowing that my life's work
was helping this son of a bitch.

08:48.332 --> 08:50.066
Please. Jesse.

08:51.836 --> 08:53.703
Look, I'm not
making any promises, man.

08:53.771 --> 08:55.038
I'll --
I'll check it out.

08:55.106 --> 08:57.273
Where can I
find this guy?

08:57.341 --> 09:00.443
He's having dinner with a buyer
on Ocean Drive in an hour.

09:00.511 --> 09:02.178
In an hour?
Mm-hmm.

09:02.246 --> 09:04.180
Guess I got to
make some phone calls.

09:07.651 --> 09:11.321
<i>Audio surveillance is</i>
<i>more difficult than it sounds.</i>

09:11.388 --> 09:13.690
<i>Taking coherent notes</i>
<i>on a half-heard conversation</i>

09:13.758 --> 09:15.158
<i>is a challenge.</i>

09:15.226 --> 09:17.127
<i>And aiming a directional mike</i>
<i>at a target</i>

09:17.194 --> 09:20.063
<i>without being too obvious</i>
<i>takes the skills of a marksman.</i>

09:20.131 --> 09:21.397
Okay.
How are we doing here?

09:21.465 --> 09:23.666
- You got the sound up?
- Yeah, it's up right here.

09:23.734 --> 09:25.435
You're lucky
you're a friend of Jesse's,

09:25.503 --> 09:28.037
'cause I'm getting a serious
crick in my neck here.

09:28.105 --> 09:30.073
Is it worth it?
Is he saying anything good?

09:30.141 --> 09:32.709
Shut up! Your dirty diplomat's
finishing his business.

09:32.777 --> 09:36.045
You know,
I like the deal.

09:36.113 --> 09:37.514
And the price
is a little high,

09:37.581 --> 09:39.282
but for what you're bringing me,
I-I don't mind spending it.

09:39.350 --> 09:41.217
I just want to know
that you can deliver.

09:41.285 --> 09:43.186
I don't want police
or customs.

09:43.254 --> 09:45.188
You know
who protects my shipments?

09:45.256 --> 09:46.489
The police.

09:46.557 --> 09:49.159
And the U.S. Customs
that you're so worried about.

09:49.226 --> 09:52.061
Diplomatic pouches
are untouchable.

09:52.129 --> 09:54.097
Your concern
is getting my money.

09:57.067 --> 10:01.004
I'll have it tomorrow morning.
9:00, soon as the bank opens.

10:01.071 --> 10:03.873
I'll be ready
for your call.

10:03.941 --> 10:05.608
Okeydokey.

10:05.676 --> 10:06.843
What?

10:06.911 --> 10:08.144
What?
What did they say?

10:08.212 --> 10:10.280
What? What's going on?
What did he say?

10:10.347 --> 10:14.684
Bad news. The deal's
not next week. It's tomorrow.

10:14.752 --> 10:16.619
So, we have to
go in tonight?

10:16.687 --> 10:17.821
Is this guy serious?

10:17.888 --> 10:19.756
That's not
how field-ops work, Ian.

10:19.824 --> 10:21.624
We got to scout.
We got to make a plan.

10:21.692 --> 10:22.826
It's gonna take a few days
at least.

10:22.893 --> 10:24.861
We got to buy ourselves
some time.

10:26.764 --> 10:28.398
Okay, how about this?

10:28.465 --> 10:30.667
Take out the sleazebag
in the silk shirt,

10:30.734 --> 10:32.902
and while Yash is scrambling
to put together another deal,

10:32.970 --> 10:34.637
we figure out how to take him out.
- I like it.

10:34.705 --> 10:36.005
Wait. We can't.

10:36.073 --> 10:37.574
Yash will get suspicious
if the buyer just disappears.

10:37.641 --> 10:39.275
No, the buyer's not gonna
disappear. The money is.

10:39.343 --> 10:41.277
Fortunately, he just told us
when he's gonna move it.

10:41.345 --> 10:43.680
Okay, but, with Mike dealing
with this Vaughn business,

10:43.747 --> 10:45.114
all we got team wise
is Fi.

10:45.182 --> 10:47.083
That's perfect. Robbing a guy
in broad daylight --

10:47.151 --> 10:49.219
that's a Fi kind of job.

